 Syntax:  .gwipe <parameter>

Results:  Wipes the messages from the gripe board.
          .gwipe <NUM> <NUM> where both number are the same is a line delete.
          UNLIKE .cmail or .csent, you will NOT be asked to verify the    
          wipe. 
          
Example:
   To wipe all messages from the board, type            : .gwipe all
   To clear the first line type                         : .gwipe          
   To clear line 10 from the board, type                : .gwipe 10        
   To clear all lines from the beginning to line 5, type: .gwipe to 5        
   To clear all lines from line 8 to the end, type      : .gwipe from 8      
   To clear all lines from line 8 to line 10, type      : .gwipe from 8 to 10
   To clear all lines except line 4, type               : .gwipe except 4     
   To clear all lines except line 4 through 9, type     : .gwipe except 4 to 9

See also: wipe, gripe, swipe, wwipe
